	<div class="featured featured_right">

	<div class="date">
		March 9, 2015	</div>
	
	
		  
	<h2><a href="/martynjones/303411/consider-big-data-not-data-warehousing">Big Data Is Not Data Warehousing</a></h2>
  
	<div class="meta">
		<div class="comment"><a href="http://smartdatacollective.com/martynjones/303411/consider-big-data-not-data-warehousing#comments" title="comments"></a></div>
		by <a href="/user/1633616">Martyn Jones</a>
	</div>
	
	<div class="body blurb-wrap">

				<div class="image">
			
			<a href="http://smartdatacollective.com/martynjones/303411/consider-big-data-not-data-warehousing"><img src="http://smartdatacollective.com/sites/smartdatacollective.com/files/imagecache/featured_right_image_204sq/Screen%20shot%202015-03-09%20at%202.21.52%20AM.png" alt="" title="" width="204" height="204" class="imagecache imagecache-featured_right_image_204sq imagecache-default imagecache-featured_right_image_204sq_default"/></a>
			
						<div class="attribution"><p><em>Data warehousing?</em></p></div>
						
		</div>
				
		<p>Big Data is not Data Warehousing, it is not the evolution of Data Warehousing and it is not a sensible and coherent alternative to Data Warehousing. No matter what certain vendors will put in their marketing brochures or stick up their noses.<a href="/martynjones/303411/consider-big-data-not-data-warehousing">[read more]</a></p>

